\newlabel{fig:noise_robustness}{{5}{26}{Noise robustness analysis across 6 noise levels ($\sigma \in [0, 0.5]$). Hensel-satisfied configurations maintain high periods even under additive Gaussian noise, while violated configurations degrade rapidly. This demonstrates that the period growth mechanism is robust to perturbations, a key property for cryptographic applications}{figure.caption.14}{}}
